(thirdQuint)Safety and Efficacy Study of Repeated Doses of DX-88 (Ecallantide) to Treat Attacks of Hereditary Angioedema (HAE).

 This is an open label trial.

 The study is designed to assess the efficacy and safety of 30 mg subcutaneous ecallantide in the treatment of acute attacks of hereditary angioedema.

 This study is designed to provide efficacy and safety data on repeated use of ecallantide.

 These data are intended to support the marketing authorization of ecallantide in the treatment of acute attacks of hereditary angioedema.

 Efficacy and safety of ecallantide will be evaluated in this study.

